Hungary May Escape Downgrade to Junk, Nomura’s Montalto Says

-- B y   Z o l t a n   S i m o n
-- 
2011-10-18T15:15:42Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-18/hungary-may-escape-downgrade-to-junk-nomura-s-montalto-says.html
Hungary may escape a downgrade of
its sovereign credit rating to junk from the lowest investment
grade, Nomura Plc economist Peter Attard Montalto said.  “We believe a downgrade will be avoided, but only
just,” London-based Montalto said in an e-mail today.  An International Monetary Fund package would “save” the
country from a downgrade, Montalto said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Zoltan Simon at 
 zsimon@bloomberg.net  